CAPE TOWN - Large parts of Cape Town are without power. City of Cape Town said that technicians were attending to a power outage in the metro's Area 2. Suburbs including Montague Gardens, Milnerton, Kensington, Century City and surrounds have been affected. Officials said that an exact time of when electricity would be restored was still unclear at this stage. The cause of the outage is not known yet. Earlier, parts of Area 7 were affected by the outage but electricity has been restored.Updates will follow and we thank our customers for their understanding. #CTNews 